[h1]1.3 - 1.2 Update & Bug Fixes[/h1]

[h2]1.2 Compatibility[/h2]
[list]
[*]Updated supported_game_version to 1.2.*
[*]Marriage validation is compatible with 1.2's new regent and celibacy restrictions (handled by character_can_marry_trigger)
[/list]

[h2]Bug Fixes[/h2]
[list]
[*][b]Fixed court limit not working[/b]: if the pop limit variable was never initialized, marriages would fire with no cap and culling would never activate. The mod now initializes a default pop limit of 150 on game start and on situation activation (for existing saves). All marriage on_actions now require the pop limit to be set before firing.
[*][b]Fixed heir's wife killed by culling[/b]: population control events now exclude all crown estate members (ruler's family) from the kill list. The culling will no longer target your ruler, heir, or their spouses.
[*][b]Fixed estate marriages ignoring pop limit[/b]: burgher, clergy, peasant, dhimmi, tribes, and cossack marriage on_actions previously only checked the pop limit conditionally. They now always enforce it.
[/list]
